class Solution {
public:
    bool doesAliceWin(string s) {
        int v = 0;
        for(char c: s)
            if(c=='a'||c=='e'||c=='i'||c=='o'||c=='u') ++v;
        return v!=0;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The game is a simple impartial game whose outcome depends only on whether the initial string contains at least one vowel. If there are any vowels, Alice can always remove the whole string on her first move and win immediately; otherwise she has no move and loses.

